schema.name: ID	Fecha	Nombres	Apellidos	Edad	Genero	Discapacidad	Tipo_discapacidad	Nivel_educacion	Ingles	Cursos	Informatica	Certificacion_competencias	Laborando	Organizacion	Teletrabajado	Internet
ID	Fecha	Nombres	Apellidos	Edad	Genero	Discapacidad	Tipo_discapacidad	Nivel_educacion	Ingles	Cursos	Informatica	Certificacion_competencias	Laborando	Organizacion	Teletrabajado	Internet

typeProperties.script:
source(output(
		NOMBRE as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> source1
source(output(
		NOMBRE as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> source2
source(output(
		ID as string,
		Fecha as string,
		Nombres as string,
		Apellidos as string,
		Edad as string,
		Genero as string,
		Discapacidad as string,
		Tipo_discapacidad as string,
		Nivel_educacion as string,
		Ingles as string,
		Cursos as string,
		Informatica as string,
		Certificacion_competencias as string,
		Laborando as string,
		Organizacion as string,
		Teletrabajado as string,
		Internet as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> source3
source1 derive(GENERO = "FEMENINO") ~> DerivedColumn2
source2 derive(GENERO = "MASCULINO") ~> DerivedColumn3
DerivedColumn2, DerivedColumn3 union(byName: true)~> Union1
Union1 derive(FUENTE = "DNP CONTEXTO") ~> DerivedColumn4
source3 derive(FUENTE = "TUNJA") ~> DerivedColumn5
DerivedColumn5 select(mapColumn(
		NOMBRE = Nombres,
		GENERO = Genero,
		FUENTE
	),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> Select1
DerivedColumn4, Select1 union(byName: true)~> Union2
Union2 derive(NOMBRE = trim(upper(NOMBRE)),
		GENERO = trim(upper(GENERO)),
		ULTIMA_LETRA = upper(substring( reverse(trim(NOMBRE)) , 1, 1)  )) ~> DerivedColumn6
DerivedColumn6 sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	partitionFileNames:['nombres_unificados.csv'],
	truncate: true,
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> sink1

source(output(
		COD_DPTO as string,
		COD_DANE as string,
		DEPARTAMENTO as string,
		MUNICIPIO as string,
		ORIP as string,
		VEREDA as string,
		MATRICULA as string,
		TIPO_PREDIO as string,
		NRO_ANOTACION as string,
		COD_NATURALEZA as string,
		NATURALEZA_JURIDICA as string,
		VALOR as string,
		DIRECCION as string,
		Divipola_Mun_0001 as string,
		ZRE_NOMBRE as string,
		SISTEMA as string,
		NRO_PROPIETARIOS as string,
		ESTADO_FOLIO as string,
		{A�O RADICACION} as string,
		LINDERO as string,
		SMMLV as string,
		RANGOS_AVALUOS as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> source1
source1 select(mapColumn(
		COD_DPTO,
		COD_DANE,
		DEPARTAMENTO,
		MUNICIPIO,
		ORIP,
		VEREDA,
		MATRICULA,
		TIPO_PREDIO,
		NRO_ANOTACION,
		COD_NATURALEZA,
		NATURALEZA_JURIDICA,
		VALOR,
		DIRECCION,
		Divipola_Mun_0001,
		ZRE_NOMBRE,
		SISTEMA,
		NRO_PROPIETARIOS,
		ESTADO_FOLIO,
		ANIO_RADICACION = {A�O RADICACION},
		LINDERO,
		SMMLV,
		RANGOS_AVALUOS
	),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> Select1
Select1 filter(TIPO_PREDIO != 'URBANO') ~> Filter1
Filter1 sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	format: 'parquet',
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> sink1
